The production of local construction chemicals would greatly reduce supply time of innovative solutions and quality products to customers. BASF, the world’s leading chemical company and a leading manufacturer of construction chemicals, said in a release that the plant producing Admixtures for concrete, will be run through a tolling agreement. “This investment is another very important step for BASF in Africa. “Our involvement in the continent is growing, and a very big role is played by BASF Construction Chemicals that is looking at strategic countries with big potential, such as Tanzania” said Michael Gotsche, Vice President, Africa. Christian Geierhaas - Vice President Construction Chemicals Middle East, West Asia, CIS & Africa said investing in Tanzania, would allow BASF Construction Chemicals to bring innovative products, technology and solutions closer to its customers in “such an important and strategic market”.